Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and markedly increased total bilirubin, suggesting possible liver dysfunction or hemolysis. Platelets are mildly elevated. Coagulation parameters (INR, aPTT) are prolonged, which may reflect hepatic dysfunction or anticoagulation. There is mild metabolic acidosis (low pH, low pCO₂, low O₂ saturation). Lipid profile is significantly abnormal with high total and LDL cholesterol. Further clinical correlation and follow-up are recommended to assess renal, hepatic, and cardiovascular status.
